(4089, 'A694B4B3-3441-46E1-8094-297358EBCF4B', 'Hey Nathan. I know you’ve been feeling sad and probably angry for the last few days. My sense is that in the heat of the moment you may not remember what people are saying to you or what you are saying to people — so I’ll help with explaining what I saw happen two nights ago. I’ve only have two expectations for you and they have never changed...1. Be respectful to people around you 2. Do not yell. Two nights ago, you were shouting at the top of your lungs, cussing left and right - to people who wanted to help you. I told you that if you continued to yell, you would not be able to stay in the house. I understand that you may be hurt by that, but my expectations of how you treat people will always be the same and will never change. My goal isn’t to hurt you. But when you are disrespectful, there are consequences. All of that said, I did not ask you to leave the house even though you woke up Orli. You left on your own and said “nitzan doesn’t have to kick me out, I’ll just go on my own.” It’s pretty important to remember that you’re not the only one living under our roof. My goal isn’t to make you upset but it is to hold you to a high standard. If you don’t learn how to manage your anger and your feelings now, it could hurt you down the road with employers, girlfriends, or anyone else you want to be close to. I love you very much and would be happy to talk about this anytime. ', 'Nitzan', 'David', '2017-11-01T12:00:53'),
